post_text: Our Child Nutrition Department is resuming the free meals for children program on Monday, September 14. See below for details on the program.
shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
September 11 at 2:31 PM ·

Good news! Beginning Monday, September 14th meals will be FREE for all children 18 & younger. Breakfast and lunch will be available for ANY child, not just students enrolled in our district. This impacts our curbside meal service and will also impact students when they return to in-person learning.

New for curbside meals: Parents/guardians who are picking up meals on behalf of the children in their care will be asked to complete and display a placard in their vehicle. You will receive the form to fill out on the first day that you participate in meal service.

We are grateful to USDA for extending the Summer Food Service Program through December.

The Laveen School District, Urban Farming, and St. Mary's Food Bank are partnering for a community food giveaway on Monday, September 14 beginning at 10:00 a.m.

Food boxes will be given away at the following school sites: Trailside Point, Paseo Pointe, Laveen School and Rogers Ranch. The event will take place in the staff parking lot.

Participants must present a government issued ID. If you do not have an Arizona ID, please provide mail that shows your name and an Arizona address.

Families who wish to participate must arrive in a vehicle. Each vehicle will receive one food box/bag. If you plan on participating in this event you must do the following:
1) Wear a mask
2) Stay in your car
3) Follow the direction of the volunteers when proceeding in line.

The event is sponsored by St. Mary's Food Bank, Positive Image Sports, Pure Heart Church, the Laveen Lions, the Laveen Baptist Church, and Fry's Food Stores. Boxes will be distributed while supplies last.

shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
July 7 at 8:55 PM ·

Applications for free and reduced-price meals for school year 2020-2021 are now available at EZMealApp.com. Apply today!

Beginning August 3rd, we will continue our curbside meal service for enrolled Laveen students only. Breakfast will be free for all students and lunch will cost $2.50. You may qualify for free or reduced-price lunches. Reduced-price lunches will cost $0.40. More details about our meal service options for the 2020-2021 school year will be forthcoming.

In accordance with CDC guidelines related to COVID-19, we are asking parents/guardians to complete the meal application online in lieu of a paper application to ensure a quick, safe and contact-less process.

post_text:
Laveen Schools to Reopen on August 3.

On June 29, Governor Doug Ducey issued Executive Order (2020-44) which delayed the opening of schools for on-site learning until August 17 at the earliest. This executive order gave school districts the option of opening on their scheduled start date using distance/online learning.

The Laveen School District has determined that, given the uncertainty of when schools will be able to open for on-site learning, we will keep our current calendar and begin the 2020-21 school year on August 3 using distance/online learning for all students.

Once the executive order is lifted, Laveen intends to move forward with the four schooling options outlined below with some students returning to school for daily on-site instruction.

Read more: www.laveenschools.org/return-to-laveen

Today Governor Doug Ducey issued Executive Order 2020-44 regarding the reopening of schools.

The order states that all schools must delay the start of in-person classes until August 17, 2020, but that schools may begin the school year on their regularly planned start date using distance/online learning.

The Laveen District will be diligently researching the matters raised by this latest executive order to develop options and recommendations for the Governing Board to consider.

On June 23, Laveen’s Reopening of Schools Task Force will provide their recommendations to the Governing Board for the 2020-21 school year. These recommendations are based on results from the recent parent and teacher surveys. The recommendations include the following options:

-Full-Year Online Learning (Laveen Online Academy)
-Flexible Distance Learning (Distance Learning with Transition to On-Site)
-Daily On-Site Learning (Full-Day, Every-Day at School)
-Estrella Foothills Global Academy (Grades K-6)

Visit https://www.laveenschools.org/return-to-laveen/ for details.

Watch the June 23 Governing Board Meeting, beginning at 4:00 p.m. and streamed live at: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EMubrMSXbWI

post_text:
All Laveen offices will reopen to the public on June 15. Offices will be open from 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. Monday – Thursday. Offices are closed on Fridays throughout the summer months.

In an effort to slow the spread of COVID-19, we are permitting only one family in the lobby at a time. We ask families to wait outside, at least six feet apart, until it is their turn. Shade will be provided. We encourage all visitors to wear a mask during their visit.

Families who are enrolling their child for the 2020-21 school year, may begin the process online through our new registration portal, www.laveenschools.org/registration. Necessary documents, as outlined on our registration page, will need to be presented in-person before your child may begin the school year.

post_text: As we transition to the summer meal program, see the schedule changes that are taking place starting this Wednesday. More details on summer meals to come.
shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
May 16 at 12:32 AM ·

As we transition into summer, our grab & go meal service program will look a little different for the remainder of May.

Next week, we will operate at our CURRENT meal locations at the CURRENT times, Monday through Wednesday. Families will receive 3 days worth of meals on Wednesday.

We will be closed Thursday, Friday and Monday for the Memorial Day holiday. 🇺🇸

Starting Tuesday, May 26th, we will transition to our NEW meal service locations, with NEW times. On Tuesday, families will receive 2 days worth of meals and Thursday, families will receive 4 days worth of meals. All meals will continue to be served grab & go style.

We will be providing an update of our summer program for June and beyond later this month. ☀️ Please share widely!

Thank you for your continued support and participation in our program.

For the first time ever, we're joining forces with six major sports leagues to launch a digital education competition like you've never seen before - the EduCup Challenge.

Students will work alongside their favorite sports teams to complete digital courses focused on teaching critical skills and healthy habits. The more students who participate, the more points their team earns, and they get one step closer to winning the 2020 EduCup (which comes with the chance to win scholarships or prizes)!

There's nothing like a little friendly competition to get students fired up about learning.

Join the challenge May 18: www.everfi.com/educup-challenge

April 20 at 11:41 PM ·

Laveen School District families are encouraged to apply for free or reduced-price meals for the CURRENT school year.

Why now?

In addition to having free/reduced-price meal benefits that would carry over for the first 30 days of the new school year, families may qualify for additional benefits now through the Families First Coronavirus Response Act and would help our district qualify for other grant funding.

If you are new to the district or have recently had a change in financial circumstances, please apply online. All information is completely confidential.

Note: All families must apply for free/reduced-price meals on an annual basis.

post_text:
Parents who would like to pick up their child's medications may do so by scheduling an appointment with one of our District Nurses.

If you prefer, you can keep your child's medication at school for the remainder of the school year. The district is able to keep your child's medication through the summer, as we have modified our end-of-year procedures and will not dispose of medications that are not picked up by parents in May. When school resumes, you will need to sign a new Medication Administration Form for the 2020/2021 school year.

You can contact our nurses by email at lsorensen@laveeneld.org or by phone/text at (602) 515-1047.

post_text: We're still feeding kids despite the school closures. Take them for a ride to any of our sites for free grab & go breakfast and lunch. Children must be present to receive a meal. Children do not need to be Laveen students.
shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
March 15 at 11:55 PM ·

In light of the school closures, our department will be providing FREE grab n' go meals at breakfast and lunch beginning tomorrow. All schools (except for Vista Del Sur) will be open daily to serve the community.

📍 All children are welcome! You do not need to be a Laveen student or resident to participate.
📍 Free meals are available to all! You do not need to qualify for free or reduced-price meals to participate.
📍 Children must be present to receive the meal.
📍 Adult meals are not available.

Keep following our page for updates.

post_text: Members of the @homedepot in Avondale and volunteers from the University of Phoenix visited Paseo Pointe School on Friday to provide hands on experiences for 3rd and 5th grade students. Fifth graders first learned how to build a wooden hockey game or spring basket. Then, they taught and assisted third grade students. This great project, developed by teacher Mr. Ren Fahey, taught the students how to follow written instructions and encouraged teamwork. See more photos on our flickr page, https://www.flickr.com/photos/laveenesd/albums

post_text: We are proud of our cafeterias for their regular A ratings by Maricopa County Environmental Health.
shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
November 12, 2019 at 3:59 PM ·

Today we are thankful for high standards in food safety. Did you know that our kitchens get at least 2 food safety inspections a year? Our schools continually obtain an "A" rating with few or zero findings. It helps that we have 25 Certified Food Safety Managers on our team and follow a comprehensive food safety plan based on HACCP principles. You can rest assured that our food is of the highest quality and is safe to eat.

#GratefulLaveenCNS #gratitudechallenge #foodsafety

The program provides lesson plans to help teach students about eco-friendly practices. Students then collect markers and ship them to Crayola for recycling.

Vista del Sur is collecting markers for another upcoming shipment.

post_text: Students participating in afterschool activities will now be able to enjoy a a hearty snack at no charge.The Super Snack program begins Monday at all Laveen schools.
shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
September 27, 2019 at 11:39 PM ·

Beginning on Monday, our cafeterias will be starting the USDA Afterschool Meals Program a.k.a. the Super Snack program. These meals will be available for students participating in after school activities, free of charge. We have designed these super snacks to be nutritious, quick and easy to eat, and delicious - giving students a chance to refuel before moving on to their activity. Whether students are practicing sports, receiving tutoring, participating in a club or attending Kids Club - we've got a meal ready for them. Here's a sneak peek at some of the great Super Snack options we've come up with.

#thisisschoollunch #LaveenChildNutrition #azschoolmeals #fuelingAZ #afterschoolmeals #supersnacks

shared_text:
Arizona School Facilities Board
September 27, 2019 at 10:07 PM ·

A new Arizona law allows school districts to build new schools if they will be overcapacity in two years (formally it had to be current year overcapacity). The change is allowing Laveen Elementary District to start construction immediately on a 92,000 square foot school set to open in FY 2021 (August 2020). It will have $14 Million in SFB funding. Here are some photos of the site in pre-construction.

post_text: Hundreds of Laveen 5th and 6th grade students from across the district participated in today's D-backs District 5 Jam, hosted by the Arizona Diamondbacks and Maricopa County Supervisor Steve Gallardo. Students were selected based on performing community service and writing a report about the experience and their feelings. Students received a ticket to today's game, lunch, and a t-shirt. They also got to walk out on to the field before the game. Governing Board member Fern Ward helped provide this opportunity for our students.

Students were selected based on performing community service and writing a report about the experience and their feelings. Students received a ticket to today's game, lunch, and a t-shirt. They also got to walk out on to the field before the game. Governing Board member Fern Ward helped provide this opportunity for our students.

Three students were recognized for receiving a perfect score in both the math and ELA sections for 2019. Congratulations Christian, Kenzie, and Taylor!

post_text: We are encouraging families to apply for free or reduced price lunches. Families that qualified last year will need to reapply before Sept. 16.
shared_text:
Laveen Child Nutrition Services
September 4, 2019 at 10:11 PM ·

Laveen schools serve free or reduced-price lunches to families that qualify based on income requirements.

Families must reapply annually. Families that qualified last year must reapply before September 16th. Visit www.EZMealApp.com to apply online today. The process is simple and applications are processed quickly. Paper applications are also available at your school's front office or cafeteria.

All families are encouraged to apply, even if they don't think they will qualify or lunches are brought from home, as this information helps to bring additional funding to our schools in the form of grants. Applications are processed year round and are kept confidential.

As a reminder, breakfast is free for all students, regardless of their meal eligibility status.
